
Docker desktop is free for learning.
Docker Desktop is not free for enterprise or commercial use.
Docker Desktop includes many tools.
e.g. Engine, CLI, Compose, Kubernetes, Buildkit, Scan etc...

Docker desktop needs Linux OS VM, so for windows we need to WSL --install/update. Windows subsystem for Linux.

Three ways to run DOcker container:
1. Local - Docker Desktop - Other Local tools:--> Rancher Desktop, dockerd, cli, k3s, Minikube.
2. Server - Docker Engine, K8s
3. Paas - CloudRun, Fargate.
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECS/latest/userguide/what-is-fargate.html
